    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup heavily incentivized by high-upside matchups, headlined by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.34) and **Junior Caminero** (76.33). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is our premier play, benefiting from a massive +19% boost against the porous 7.83 xERA of the opposing starter; his elite sprint speed makes him the primary engine for our scarcity-driven SB strategy today. **Junior Caminero** provides the safest floor in the order, as his +8% SP skill adjustment and prime #2 spot in the lineup offer the highest probability of run production. Meanwhile, **Kazuma Okamoto** (61.55) and **Chase Meidroth** (60.91) round out our recommended starts, with **Chase Meidroth** particularly well-positioned to capitalize on his +10% order bonus at the top of the lineup despite facing a neutral matchup.\n\nStrategic benching remains critical to preserving our game caps, as evidenced by **Dillon Dingler** (33.08), who failed to clear the 40.0 floor due to a -15% dynamic platoon penalty against a tough arm in Ritchie (2.92 xERA). We are also navigating a significant roster disruption, with heavy hitters **Trea Turner**, **Yordan Alvarez**, and **Kyle Schwarber** all sidelined by rainouts, forcing the Zebras to lean on depth pieces like **Carson Benge** and **Caleb Durbin**. While **Gary Sanchez** (58.32) and **Luke Raley** (58.36) hover near the \"Strong\" threshold, they remain essential volatility mitigators in a day where weather-related postponements have removed our primary power anchors from the board. Monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Josh Smith**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** as potential pinch-hit contingencies should late-inning leverage opportunities arise.",
